A TEENAGE girl is scared to return to school after four others beat her up on her way home on Monday, 14 February. The girls accused the 16-year-old of gossiping about them and attacked her, leaving her bleeding. The grade 10 pupil at Motlalaohle Secondary School in Botlokwa, Limpopo, said she still had a wound to her left eye, a neck injury and general body pain. She said a video of the attack was also circulated on social media, subjecting her to cyberbullying. ALSO READ: VISIT TO BAE'S MKHUKHU ENDS IN TEARS! She said reading comments hurt her so much she deactivated her Facebook account. “Some pupils from the school were making jokes about what happened. I’m so scared of the perpetrators,” she said. Social Development MEC Nkakareng Rakgoale condemned the incident. “We referred the matter to our social workers and they’ll speedily get in touch with the family and victim to provide psychosocial support. “We’ve also referred the matter to the education department and SAPS,” said the MEC